svt_i2c_slave_monitor_transaction_report_callback Class Reference

Inheritance diagram for class svt_i2c_slave_monitor_transaction_report_callback:

List of all members.

Detailed Description

This callback class is used to generate Transaction summary information relative to the svt_i2c_slave_monitor component. Transactions are reported on as they occur, for inclusion in the log.

  function void
 svt_i2c_slave_monitor_transaction_report_callback::new
 (  svt_sequence_item_report sys_xact_report , bit enable_log_report , bit enable_file_report , bit enable_local_summaries = 1, string name = "svt_i2c_slave_monitor_transaction_report_callback"  ) 

Creates a new instance of this class, with a reference to the Transaction report.

sys_xact_report - Transaction report we are contributing to.

enable_log_report - Indicates whether reporting to a log should be enabled.

enable_file_report - Indicates whether reporting to a file should be enabled.

enable_local_summaries - Indicates whether the callbacks should create localized summaries.

name - Instance name.

  function void
 svt_i2c_slave_monitor_transaction_report_callback::set_impl_display_depth
 (  svt_i2c_slave_monitor mon , int impl_display_depth , bit modify_system , bit modify_local , bit modify_log , bit modify_file  ) 

Controls the implementation display depth for a Transaction summary log and/or file group.

mon - Component reporting the Transaction. Used to identify log and file group names.

impl_display_depth - New implementation display depth. Can be set to any any non-negative value.

modify_system - Indicates whether this change is applicable to the system reporting.

modify_local - Indicates whether this change is applicable to the local reporting.

modify_log - Indicates whether this change is applicable to the log reporting.

modify_file - Indicates whether this change is applicable to the file reporting.
